The paper deals with domain generalization in computer vision, specifically in the context of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model for end-to-end DG learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of a new benchmark dataset, which could fall under several sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
